            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I had a similar problem a while ago. The Problem was that neovim ships lua treesitter highlighting but not indentation (indents.scm). This is still handled via the external nvim-treesitter\n\nI tried your code example and treesitter-formating/indent, works as expected.\n\nDid you install and enable the external indents for lua?\n\n```lua\nvim.pack.add({\n  { src = \"https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter\" },\n})\nrequire('nvim-treesitter').install({\n   'lua'\n})\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\n  pattern = {\n     'lua',\n  },\n  callback = function()\n    vim.treesitter.start()\n    vim.bo.indentexpr = \"v:lua.require'nvim-treesitter'.indentexpr()\"\n  end\n})\n\n```",
