            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Hmm, it seems that the Lua indent plugin doesn't work with treesitter highlighting. It works after `vim.treesitter.stop()`.\n\nYes, that's correct (and the reason why I keep pushing back on just \"make treesitter default for syntax\"). Concretely, the issue is that `indent.vim` is using `synIDattr` to check for comments (see the reproducing example).\n\nSince full treesitter indents in core is a ways off, my recommendation would be to simply translate `indent/lua.vim` 1:1 to Lua and use either`vim.treesitter.get_captures_at_pos` or `vim.treesitter.get_node():type()` to check for comments at the given pos instead. (This should be a simple project for an LLM.)\n\n(Implementation of the `includexpr` goes in `runtime/lua/vim/_ftplugin/lua.lua`; setting/restoring goes in `indent/lua.lua`; see `ftplugin/lua.lua` for examples.)",
