        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "So a lot of question again..\n```\nstatus quo:\na) tree-sitter disabled and indent/lua.vim (comment works and commentblock works)\nb) tree-sitter disabled and indent/lua.lua (comment works and commentblock \"doesn't work\")\n\nc) tree-sitter enabled and indent/lua.vim  (comment doesnt work and commentblock \"doesn't work\")\nd) tree-sitter enabled and indent/lua.lua  (comment works and commentblock \"doesn't work\")\n```\n1. How should we proceed? Wait for becoming core? Provide a temporary fix?\n2. If temp fix...What is the correct way to hook-in the right file (vim/lua) after checking if treesitter is started? Is this even possible? I tried to find a similar example somewhere in the src/docs, but I couldn't find one.\n3. Just provide the `indent/lua.lua` as a GH-Discussion and users should paste it in their own runtimepath\nhttps://github.com/gx089/neovim/blob/master/runtime/indent/lua.lua\n",
